#: ../new/civilianenemies.rst:4
msgid "Civilian Enemies"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/civilianenemies.rst:6
msgid ""
"In :game:`Red Alert 2` the environment is pretty much friendly and "
"factions do not have to fear an attack of inhabitants of the territory "
"they are fighting in. The engine would not know how to deal with them, "
"and this is what :game:`Ares` changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/civilianenemies.rst:15
msgid "Treat Civilians as Enemies"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/civilianenemies.rst:17
msgid ""
":game:`Yuri's Revenge` makes a distinction between single player and "
"multi player games. In multiplay matches all objects belonging to a house"
" with :tag:`MultiplayPassive=yes` are considered neutral, with the "
"exception of tech and occupiable structures. In single player missions "
"units are not considered neutral if they are :tag:`Insignificant=no`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/civilianenemies.rst:26
msgid ":tagdef:`[TechnoType]CivilianEnemy=boolean`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/civilianenemies.rst:24
msgid ""
"Whether this unit is considered an enemy when auto-acquiring a target. "
"Enabling this prevents a unit of this type to be considered neutral in "
"multiplayer matches. Defaults to :value:`no`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/civilianenemies.rst:34
msgid "Repelling Civilian Attacks"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/civilianenemies.rst:36
msgid ""
"If civilians are not recognized as dangerous, only units or structures "
"attacked by such neutral units will retaliate against them. This way "
"units like the Visceroid or the Tiberium Fiend can bring down a house's "
"buildings one by one."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/civilianenemies.rst:40
msgid ""
"This new tag makes the AI's or the player's unit smarter in defending "
"against such threats as civilians attacking a power plant will be "
"repelled by all allies in range, or alligators eating Engineers with "
"armed bystanders just idling."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/civilianenemies.rst:48
msgid ":tagdef:`[CombatDamage]AutoRepel=boolean`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/civilianenemies.rst:45
msgid ""
"Whether AI players will consider civilian units attacking allied objects "
"as enemy when auto-acquiring targets. This makes units nearby help "
"protect against an offender. Otherwise, only the attacked unit "
"retaliates. Defaults to :value:`no`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/civilianenemies.rst:54
msgid ":tagdef:`[CombatDamage]PlayerAutoRepel=boolean`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/civilianenemies.rst:51
msgid ""
"Whether human players will consider civilian units attacking allied "
"objects as enemy when auto-acquiring targets. This makes units nearby "
"help protect against an offender. Otherwise, only the attacked unit "
"retaliates. Defaults to :value:`no`."
msgstr ""

